rComments: Professor Donia is an amazing professor who will give you guidance from the very start of the term in order to be successful in her course. If you read the textbook and attend the lectures to ask questions, you will do very well in her course. Definitely one of the best OB professors you will get

This professor is both good and bad. The mid term and final exam were both very easy, but the bi-weekly case studies where graded very hard,but in general the grading was very easy. However, prepare to read the book. The professor is very boring, in fact I stopped attending lectures very early, but got A+ because I read the book and had good notes

I have no idea why all of the past ratings for Professor Donia are bad. I began the semester desperately trying to switch sections due to the previous reviews but I am glad I didnt. Her lectures were informative and clear, she knows the information and is great at answering questions. The midterm and final were both fair if not too easy.

She replies to all the emails quickly and she is willing to answer the questions in zoom class. Mid-term was a bit tough and the final was alright. However, She didn't upload the slides instead she wants us to make our own notes. I also have my own notes but I don't have time to rewatch all the lectures to see her notes again.
Professor was alright. Her mid-term was tough and she didn't upload any slides which are bad things. I won't take her again in the future but her final was easy and fair.
No wonder this professor doesn't have a lot of good reviews.

Haven't finished the course yet, but I must say that this professor is extremely tough on exams. Although she is a nice person, her lectures are extremely boring and the grading is extremely tough. Taking her class was the worst mistake I ever made, even after reading the comments.
Worst mistake i made by taking her class even after reading comments. She is unorganized, rigid and very linear. Gets confused or irritated if you question on grading. Avoid!!!

Professor Donia is honestly so kind and she cares about her students :)! She gives good feedback and is easy to reach by email. Her lectures for OB are also easy to understand. Reading the textbook helps a lot as most of the class material is also in the text in more detail .Overall, great class and great prof. It is not hard at all to get an A.

Although she is a nice person, her lectures are extremely boring and the grading is very tough. If you miss one word from a definition, you'll lose points. Take the course with a different prof if you want to do well in it

Her lectures are painfully boring and she gets very flustered and uncomfortable, almost stressed, in front of the class. This is especially the case when questioned by students about her grading criteria. You will have to know every definition in the textbook word for word and you may, just may get a decent grade. Her grading is extremely difficult

Her lectures are painfully boring. Gets very flustered and uncomfortable, almost stressed, in front of the class. This is especially the case when questioned by students about her grading criteria. Most students who submit their midterm for regrading received a lower mark than the initial. She's excessive. It's HR. Like let's calm down.
She's really nice, but won't accept anything less than exact definitions from the textbook
Did not enjoy this class at all because of this professor.
Incredibly strict on grading during midterm.
Hardest professor I have ever had
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Haven't finish the course yet, but I have to say that this profs is really tough on exam. The questions on her exam was not clear, and if you want to get points you must be answered almost exactly same words as the textbook described. On midterm exam review, most students were questioned about her grading criteria.
Great prof! As long as you read the textbook and pay attention in class its an easy A
Refused anything but exact definitions on exams. One insignificant word off and you wouldn't get the mark.  Slept like a baby through her lectures though so there is that...
Midterm answers must have word-for-word definitions. Lots of group case studies during semester. Textbook is a must.

The class  is alot of memorization and the textbook is essential. She's a good prof who cares although she gets kind of stressed sometimes and really dislikes chatter. Your answers on midterm must be word for word from textbook or lecture!

Nice enough prof, but super dry material and her lectures are boorrrriinnnggg. That being said, if you need help or have questions, she's more than happy to help. The exam material is pretty predictable and reasonable; just make sure to write down precise definitions.
Okay prof. She's a good lecturer but treats the class like children. If you take a course with her prepare for a trip back to grade 6.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Her lectures are engaging and she really explains things better than the textbook. Memorize her definitions instead of the textbooks tho, so take notes. The midterms were short answer questions that she looks for specific definitions, but final was simple multiple choice questions only! There are group assignments every 2-3 weeks (very simple)!

Great prof and very easy class but when it comes to marking midterms she looks for very specific answers. Students are losing marks for not using certain words in their definitions. Also, not very helpful if you talk to her; she has no interest in looking at your midtermcase, she will just tell you to get it remarked by the TA.
This is one of the best profs at Telfer. She is super available for her students. She'll explain and reexplain untill I got it.  Really nice.

This prof cared so much about the class, she was extremely fair and patient. She wasn't the best at engaging the class, she liked to stay behind the podium and read off her notes, but she was light-hearted and a joy to spend 3 hours with. Really easy to get an A.
Like the ideas and pedagogy. She does not put into practice concepts she teaches in class.
Great prof. Explains the concepts well. Responds to e-mails immediately, and is very helpful! Do your readings!!! Midterm is easy (short answer), final was all MC a bit harder.

Read the textbook. Her slides are useless and she doesn't bother posting them. She isn't very helpful when you ask her questions because she feels "it provides you with an advantage". Midterm was tough, but final was easy to make up for it.
